1
00:00:37,350 --> 00:00:39,060
EPISODE 10

2
00:00:40,561 --> 00:00:42,647
A Chinese restaurant owner.

3
00:00:44,065 --> 00:00:45,441
Better than I expected.

4
00:00:47,860 --> 00:00:51,364
Hey, what are you doing?
We meet after ten years.

5
00:00:51,447 --> 00:00:54,950
Even if you can't pretend to be happy,
shouldn't you at least offer me some tea?

6
00:00:56,494 --> 00:00:59,789
I don't think we're on terms
to sit and have tea.

7
00:00:59,872 --> 00:01:01,999
Hey, no need to be so guarded.

8
00:01:02,083 --> 00:01:04,835
I just came to see how you were doing.

9
00:01:06,504 --> 00:01:08,214
I was always curious.

10
00:01:08,673 --> 00:01:10,966
The traitor to his country,
Jeong Ho-myeong.

11
00:01:11,300 --> 00:01:14,804
How miserably is he living?

12
00:01:15,846 --> 00:01:18,724
But here you are with a cute son

13
00:01:18,974 --> 00:01:22,687
and doing better than I expected.
Good for you.

14
00:01:22,853 --> 00:01:25,106
Leave my family out of this.

15
00:01:26,982 --> 00:01:28,484
I didn't mean anything by it.

16
00:01:28,901 --> 00:01:33,072
I was just happy to see
that a junior I was fond of is doing well.

17
00:01:33,489 --> 00:01:35,825
Oh, right. Come to think of it

18
00:01:36,367 --> 00:01:38,369
there was another junior I was fond of.

19
00:01:42,415 --> 00:01:44,375
Team Leader Jo Seong-won, I mean.

20
00:01:45,501 --> 00:01:46,711
What a shame.

21
00:01:47,211 --> 00:01:50,673
If it weren't
for that pathetic sense of justice

22
00:01:51,132 --> 00:01:54,093
he'd have a good position
at the NIS by now

23
00:01:55,094 --> 00:01:57,930
and be living comfortably.

24
00:01:58,013 --> 00:02:01,142
Instead, his leg is ruined,
and he's a drifter.

25
00:02:01,642 --> 00:02:05,438
It's a real shame, isn't it?

26
00:02:07,356 --> 00:02:08,774
Ho-myeong.

27
00:02:09,358 --> 00:02:12,570
Ten years ago and even now

28
00:02:14,155 --> 00:02:15,990
you could have just let it go.

29
00:02:16,782 --> 00:02:20,745
Why do you have to make things
so complicated?

30
00:02:22,747 --> 00:02:26,584
This time as well,
do you and everyone around you

31
00:02:27,585 --> 00:02:29,754
have to be destroyed
before you learn your lesson?

32
00:02:39,513 --> 00:02:41,182
This isn't like you.

33
00:02:41,891 --> 00:02:44,685
- What?
- Coming here in person

34
00:02:44,769 --> 00:02:48,147
and making threats
using my family and Jo Seong-won.

35
00:02:48,898 --> 00:02:51,859
The Han Gyeong-wook I knew
at the National Intelligence Service

36
00:02:51,942 --> 00:02:53,569
wasn't the type

37
00:02:53,652 --> 00:02:56,822
to give friendly warnings
when something got in his way.

38
00:02:57,573 --> 00:02:59,617
He would have just wiped it all out.

39
00:03:12,213 --> 00:03:14,590
So why are you acting this way?

40
00:03:16,842 --> 00:03:20,805
It suddenly reminds me
of something you drilled into me.

41
00:03:21,180 --> 00:03:23,390
When infiltrating enemy lines,
maintain total situational awareness.

42
00:03:23,474 --> 00:03:26,644
Especially, pay close attention
to the enemy's armaments.

43
00:03:27,770 --> 00:03:29,855
Whatever the enemy might be holding
in their hands

44
00:03:30,189 --> 00:03:31,899
never take your eyes off them.

45
00:03:34,944 --> 00:03:36,111
You remember, don't you?

46
00:03:37,029 --> 00:03:38,614
Yes.

47
00:03:39,073 --> 00:03:42,952
I'm glad to see my lessons stuck with you.

48
00:03:44,411 --> 00:03:45,621
But, Ho-myeong.

49
00:03:46,622 --> 00:03:47,832
Do I really

50
00:03:48,833 --> 00:03:50,835
need to be on guard around you?

51
00:03:51,293 --> 00:03:54,672
Well, if you have something to hide,
then I suppose you should be.

52
00:03:56,799 --> 00:04:01,178
You've changed a lot.
Making such pathetic threats.

53
00:04:01,303 --> 00:04:04,515
Why don't you find out for yourself
if they're pathetic or not?

54
00:04:09,937 --> 00:04:13,440
You seem to have a big misunderstanding.

55
00:04:14,859 --> 00:04:16,110
I didn't

56
00:04:17,695 --> 00:04:19,905
come here to negotiate with you.

57
00:04:22,950 --> 00:04:25,202
I have no intention of negotiating either.

58
00:04:26,120 --> 00:04:27,955
I'm simply informing you.

59
00:04:28,539 --> 00:04:30,291
Since you seem to be in the dark
about something.

60
00:04:38,090 --> 00:04:39,133
Good grief.

61
00:04:40,134 --> 00:04:42,469
There's no point
in talking about this anymore.

62
00:04:42,553 --> 00:04:45,264
Yes, I agree this conversation
has gone on for too long.

63
00:04:46,599 --> 00:04:47,808
Fine.

64
00:04:48,350 --> 00:04:51,353
If you're so determined
to see this through to the end

65
00:04:51,896 --> 00:04:53,439
I'll give you what you want.

66
00:04:53,522 --> 00:04:54,899
See you around, Ho-myeong.

67
00:04:56,025 --> 00:04:57,151
Oh, right.

68
00:04:58,235 --> 00:05:02,239
And give my regards
to Team Leader Jo Seong-won.

69
00:05:21,717 --> 00:05:25,262
Ho-myeong. Hey, that man who just left...

70
00:05:25,346 --> 00:05:26,972
That was Han Gyeong-wook, right?

71
00:05:27,181 --> 00:05:31,310
I heard you were an NIS agent.
Did you know him?

72
00:05:41,278 --> 00:05:42,404
So then

73
00:05:43,989 --> 00:05:47,576
the person who framed the Director
and forced you to resign

74
00:05:48,077 --> 00:05:50,663
was the other candidate, Han Gyeong-wook?

75
00:05:51,538 --> 00:05:52,706
That's right.

76
00:05:53,624 --> 00:05:56,085
Chairman Do of Heaven Capital
and Heaven Casino

77
00:05:56,168 --> 00:05:59,213
and Candidate Han Gyeong-wook
are all in it together.

78
00:06:01,298 --> 00:06:05,302
Those guys are plotting something
on Yeongseon Island.

79
00:06:08,639 --> 00:06:12,351
That day, without any real explanation

80
00:06:12,434 --> 00:06:15,813
I suddenly told you to stop
helping the victims.

81
00:06:16,730 --> 00:06:19,441
- I'm sorry about that.
- Oh, no, Mr. Kim.

82
00:06:19,525 --> 00:06:21,610
You only said that
because you were worried.

83
00:06:21,694 --> 00:06:22,945
Right.

84
00:06:25,906 --> 00:06:27,324
But, O-ran

85
00:06:28,242 --> 00:06:30,786
I'm telling you this
because I'm truly worried.

86
00:06:30,869 --> 00:06:31,996
Any further than this

87
00:06:32,788 --> 00:06:34,540
don't try to do anything.

88
00:06:35,082 --> 00:06:38,669
This isn't just a matter
of helping the victims.

89
00:06:39,712 --> 00:06:41,672
If they find out about this

90
00:06:42,381 --> 00:06:45,384
you and the others
who are interfering with their business

91
00:06:45,926 --> 00:06:47,553
and even the people around you...

92
00:06:49,263 --> 00:06:51,098
They will never leave you alone.

93
00:06:55,853 --> 00:06:59,231
Jeong Ho-myeong came to see me yesterday.

94
00:06:59,314 --> 00:07:01,608
Oh, yes, I heard.

95
00:07:03,944 --> 00:07:07,531
About what happened
to your husband in the past...

96
00:07:08,323 --> 00:07:09,742
He told me all about it.

97
00:07:10,159 --> 00:07:13,287
He said he knows
exactly what kind of people they are.

98
00:07:15,164 --> 00:07:19,418
He said he would
take care of Han Gyeong-wook himself.

99
00:07:22,296 --> 00:07:25,174
For an NIS agent who's now a civilian

100
00:07:25,674 --> 00:07:28,260
to push himself to take on Han Gyeong-wook

101
00:07:29,845 --> 00:07:32,014
there's a sense of duty, of course.

102
00:07:33,390 --> 00:07:35,559
But the desire to protect his family

103
00:07:35,642 --> 00:07:37,186
must be the biggest reason.

104
00:07:38,270 --> 00:07:39,313
Yes.

105
00:08:20,687 --> 00:08:23,607
- It's been a while, Chairman Hwang.
- It's been a while?

106
00:08:24,191 --> 00:08:27,986
A loyal scumbag like you should just
stay by Deputy Director Han's side.

107
00:08:28,070 --> 00:08:32,199
What brings you all the way out here
on this old man's special day?

108
00:08:32,282 --> 00:08:34,034
And you didn't even bring any tofu.

109
00:08:34,118 --> 00:08:35,828
It's not like you plan on
living a clean life

110
00:08:36,453 --> 00:08:37,704
so what's the point in you eating any?

111
00:08:38,038 --> 00:08:40,374
Well, I guess you have a point.

112
00:08:40,499 --> 00:08:44,628
I'll have to get some blood on my hands
to slit Deputy Director Han's throat.

113
00:08:44,962 --> 00:08:46,171
Right?

114
00:08:48,841 --> 00:08:50,467
What's with that look?

115
00:08:50,676 --> 00:08:52,970
You let me rot in prison for ten years

116
00:08:53,053 --> 00:08:54,471
and now you let me out.

117
00:08:54,555 --> 00:08:56,515
So did you expect me
to bow down in gratitude?

118
00:08:58,976 --> 00:09:01,145
Let's stop with the pointless mind games.

119
00:09:01,478 --> 00:09:02,688
Aren't you curious

120
00:09:03,063 --> 00:09:06,400
about why the Deputy Director let you go?

121
00:09:11,238 --> 00:09:12,739
THE HOLY BIBLE

122
00:09:12,948 --> 00:09:15,117
The Lord has spoken.

123
00:09:15,534 --> 00:09:18,370
Proverbs 18:13.

124
00:09:19,746 --> 00:09:22,457
"To answer before listening

125
00:09:22,541 --> 00:09:26,086
that is folly and shame."

126
00:09:26,587 --> 00:09:30,883
Right. Since the Lord has spoken,
I'll at least hear your reason.

127
00:09:32,968 --> 00:09:34,803
So where's Deputy Director Han now?

128
00:09:35,179 --> 00:09:37,431
ORAN CHINESE RESTAURANT

129
00:09:37,514 --> 00:09:38,765
Mr. Kim.

130
00:09:39,766 --> 00:09:42,269
Hey, O-ran.

131
00:09:42,769 --> 00:09:45,939
What are you doing here?
What if those gangsters followed you?

132
00:09:46,023 --> 00:09:47,691
With Dad and you holding out like this

133
00:09:47,774 --> 00:09:50,319
without even closing up,
how could I not come?

134
00:09:52,321 --> 00:09:55,157
Honestly, your father's so stubborn.

135
00:09:56,491 --> 00:09:57,826
Where's Ho-myeong?

136
00:09:57,910 --> 00:10:00,078
He couldn't persuade your dad,
so he slept here.

137
00:10:02,039 --> 00:10:03,790
Hey, about yesterday.

138
00:10:03,874 --> 00:10:05,876
You know Han Gyeong-wook,
the candidate for mayor of Imcheon?

139
00:10:05,959 --> 00:10:07,419
He came here.

140
00:10:07,961 --> 00:10:10,172
- Han Gyeong-wook?
- Yes.

141
00:10:10,505 --> 00:10:13,383
To be honest, I was skeptical
about Ho-myeong being from the NIS.

142
00:10:13,467 --> 00:10:14,843
But I think it's actually true.

143
00:10:15,093 --> 00:10:16,637
It looked like he was here
to see Ho-myeong.

144
00:10:37,449 --> 00:10:39,785
- What are you doing here?
- Gosh, you scared me.

145
00:10:40,118 --> 00:10:41,328
Why are you here?

146
00:10:42,037 --> 00:10:43,705
We need to talk for a minute.

147
00:10:47,960 --> 00:10:51,546
I heard Han Gyeong-wook
was here yesterday.

148
00:10:51,838 --> 00:10:54,091
He's the one, isn't he?
The one who framed you

149
00:10:54,174 --> 00:10:55,968
and got you kicked out in the past.

150
00:10:57,094 --> 00:10:58,095
Yeah.

151
00:10:58,637 --> 00:11:00,055
Mr. Kim told me

152
00:11:00,806 --> 00:11:03,392
that he's an extremely dangerous person.

153
00:11:03,475 --> 00:11:06,270
Are you going to be okay?

154
00:11:07,062 --> 00:11:08,313
I'm fine.

155
00:11:09,064 --> 00:11:11,650
You, your father, and our Ji-woo...

156
00:11:11,733 --> 00:11:14,194
I'll do whatever it takes to make sure
no harm comes to any of you.

157
00:11:14,278 --> 00:11:16,029
No, I'm not worried about us.
I'm talking about you.

158
00:11:16,113 --> 00:11:17,906
I'm asking if you'll be okay.

159
00:11:17,990 --> 00:11:20,075
Is it okay for you to go up
against someone that dangerous?

160
00:11:22,995 --> 00:11:25,914
What's this? Are you worried about me?

161
00:11:28,375 --> 00:11:31,503
You're our Ji-woo's father.
How could I not be worried?

162
00:11:36,425 --> 00:11:38,218
I've been thinking.

163
00:11:39,136 --> 00:11:41,888
Just like you said, what if all of us

164
00:11:42,431 --> 00:11:44,558
get off Yeongseon Island for a while?

165
00:11:44,683 --> 00:11:47,102
I'll do my best to convince my dad.

166
00:11:47,185 --> 00:11:48,228
No.

167
00:11:48,854 --> 00:11:50,105
I can't go.

168
00:11:50,856 --> 00:11:53,650
I have to resolve this myself,
no matter what.

169
00:11:53,734 --> 00:11:56,653
- No, please don't say that.
- As you've probably heard

170
00:11:56,737 --> 00:12:00,532
Han Gyeong-wook
is planning something on Yeongseon Island.

171
00:12:00,615 --> 00:12:02,576
If that jerk actually becomes mayor

172
00:12:02,659 --> 00:12:05,954
there will be far more victims
than we're seeing now.

173
00:12:07,873 --> 00:12:09,875
I couldn't stop him ten years ago

174
00:12:10,834 --> 00:12:12,711
but this time,
I have to stop him no matter what.

175
00:12:23,138 --> 00:12:24,431
You remember, right?

176
00:12:25,766 --> 00:12:28,393
What you said on the day
our Ji-woo was born.

177
00:12:30,687 --> 00:12:35,192
You said you'd never let Ji-woo
grow up lonely like you did.

178
00:12:36,068 --> 00:12:38,987
That no matter what,
you'd always be by his side

179
00:12:39,071 --> 00:12:41,740
until he became an adult. That promise.

180
00:12:43,617 --> 00:12:44,868
Keep your promise.

181
00:12:53,001 --> 00:12:55,504
I'll find a way to convince my dad.

182
00:12:56,046 --> 00:12:59,299
You just go and take care of
that Han Gyeong-wook guy

183
00:12:59,758 --> 00:13:01,385
and come back.

184
00:13:01,468 --> 00:13:02,803
I'll be waiting.

185
00:13:04,471 --> 00:13:05,722
Okay.

186
00:13:37,587 --> 00:13:39,548
- Did she see us?
- I can't look.

187
00:13:40,298 --> 00:13:42,884
- Is she gone?
- Did she catch on?

188
00:13:43,635 --> 00:13:45,512
How diligent.

189
00:13:50,225 --> 00:13:51,476
Yes, go ahead.

190
00:13:53,353 --> 00:13:54,396
What?

191
00:13:56,648 --> 00:13:58,942
You just said that Han Gyeong-wook came
knowing everything.

192
00:13:59,025 --> 00:14:00,986
Then shouldn't you be lying low for now?

193
00:14:01,069 --> 00:14:03,238
I've bought us some time.

194
00:14:03,822 --> 00:14:06,616
But I think we need to make a move
before he catches on.

195
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:09,578
Among everything you've found out so far

196
00:14:09,661 --> 00:14:12,873
is there anything that could be
an immediate blow to Han Gyeong-wook?

197
00:14:12,956 --> 00:14:15,250
Well, there's nothing decisive

198
00:14:15,667 --> 00:14:17,043
but I'm starting to get the picture

199
00:14:17,169 --> 00:14:19,629
of what Han Gyeong-wook is up to
on Yeongseon Island.

200
00:14:20,172 --> 00:14:22,007
The Yeongseon Island development project.

201
00:14:22,591 --> 00:14:25,552
It's not as simple
as designating Yeongseon Island

202
00:14:25,635 --> 00:14:27,304
a special tourist zone to develop it.

203
00:14:27,387 --> 00:14:29,890
I don't think its intentions
are so transparent.

204
00:14:30,307 --> 00:14:32,934
You know that company,
Yeongseon Future Development

205
00:14:33,018 --> 00:14:34,144
headed by Do Hyeon-tae?

206
00:14:34,227 --> 00:14:35,520
I looked into it.

207
00:14:36,980 --> 00:14:38,899
The investors
are foreign companies with ties

208
00:14:38,982 --> 00:14:40,901
to the People's Republic of China
and Japan.

209
00:14:40,984 --> 00:14:42,235
And every single one of these companies

210
00:14:42,319 --> 00:14:44,863
is suspected of being involved
with the yakuza.

211
00:14:45,447 --> 00:14:46,490
Isn't that strange?

212
00:14:46,615 --> 00:14:49,159
Why would companies
tied to criminal organizations

213
00:14:49,242 --> 00:14:52,329
jump into the Yeongseon Island
special tourist zone development project?

214
00:14:53,163 --> 00:14:54,539
If they're tied to criminal organizations

215
00:14:54,623 --> 00:14:56,791
this is no longer just a simple
development project.

216
00:14:57,250 --> 00:14:59,503
There must be some other motive.

217
00:15:00,712 --> 00:15:04,341
If I piece together everything
I've figured out so far...

218
00:15:06,426 --> 00:15:07,427
Heaven Capital has been using

219
00:15:07,511 --> 00:15:10,972
illegal debt collection tactics
on Yeongseon Island residents

220
00:15:11,056 --> 00:15:12,390
to secure their land

221
00:15:12,766 --> 00:15:15,268
and using the money
laundered through Heaven Casino

222
00:15:15,352 --> 00:15:19,231
they've been steadily moving forward
with the project behind the scenes.

223
00:15:19,856 --> 00:15:22,442
If Han Gyeong-wook gets elected mayor

224
00:15:22,526 --> 00:15:24,402
he'll lift the regulations
on Yeongseon Island

225
00:15:24,486 --> 00:15:27,781
and push this project forward
full-scale all at once.

226
00:15:27,906 --> 00:15:29,115
So...

227
00:15:30,617 --> 00:15:33,161
We need to do something before that

228
00:15:33,745 --> 00:15:35,872
but there are no traces of Han Gyeong-wook

229
00:15:35,956 --> 00:15:37,791
in either Heaven Capital or Heaven Casino.

230
00:15:37,999 --> 00:15:40,502
I mean, if we could at least prove
that the money from both places

231
00:15:40,585 --> 00:15:43,213
went to Han Gyeong-wook,
or find a record of it

232
00:15:43,296 --> 00:15:45,173
we'd have something to prosecute him with.

233
00:15:46,758 --> 00:15:48,176
You know very well

234
00:15:48,260 --> 00:15:50,470
just how meticulous Han Gyeong-wook is.

235
00:15:51,388 --> 00:15:52,639
It looks like

236
00:15:52,722 --> 00:15:56,059
it will take some time
to secure solid evidence.

237
00:15:58,812 --> 00:16:00,605
The election is right around the corner.

238
00:16:00,689 --> 00:16:02,524
There's no more time to waste.

239
00:16:03,441 --> 00:16:05,068
If it's too difficult for you

240
00:16:05,193 --> 00:16:08,947
- I'll find the evidence my own way.
- Your own way?

241
00:16:09,364 --> 00:16:11,199
I'll tell you after I have it.

242
00:16:12,576 --> 00:16:14,911
Prosecutor, please continue
your investigation

243
00:16:14,995 --> 00:16:16,871
of the people around Han Gyeong-wook.

244
00:16:16,955 --> 00:16:19,583
Okay, I'll contact you right away
if I find anything.

245
00:16:19,666 --> 00:16:20,917
Yes, understood.

246
00:16:29,926 --> 00:16:32,554
Hey, Gang Beom-ryong. It's me.

247
00:16:33,555 --> 00:16:35,724
Bring Bulgae and come
to the camper van right now.

248
00:16:38,268 --> 00:16:40,604
- Chief Kim! Perfect timing.
- Yes.

249
00:16:46,443 --> 00:16:49,446
- About what I mentioned before.
- Yes.

250
00:16:49,529 --> 00:16:51,448
I think we need to speed things up.

251
00:16:51,990 --> 00:16:54,326
Let's dig into the people
around Han Gyeong-wook.

252
00:16:54,409 --> 00:16:55,535
Get all the details.

253
00:16:56,745 --> 00:16:59,205
Prosecutor, I don't think I can do it.

254
00:16:59,581 --> 00:17:02,584
- What?
- The Chief Prosecutor

255
00:17:02,876 --> 00:17:06,463
told me to report your every move
to him without you knowing.

256
00:17:06,630 --> 00:17:11,301
If you give me orders like this,
I have no choice but to report it.

257
00:17:16,014 --> 00:17:17,849
But he told you to do it
without my knowledge.

258
00:17:17,932 --> 00:17:19,768
Are you sure
you should be telling me this?

259
00:17:19,851 --> 00:17:23,772
Because I work with you,
not the Chief Prosecutor.

260
00:17:23,855 --> 00:17:27,609
Even if I get in trouble for it,
I thought it was right to tell you.

261
00:17:30,403 --> 00:17:31,821
Then how about this?

262
00:17:31,905 --> 00:17:34,240
Of all the people around Han Gyeong-wook

263
00:17:34,908 --> 00:17:36,493
let's start with our Chief Prosecutor.

264
00:17:36,576 --> 00:17:38,745
- Yes. What?
- Yes.

265
00:17:39,954 --> 00:17:42,707
Our Chief Prosecutor. My goodness.

266
00:17:44,167 --> 00:17:47,379
I was going to let it slide,
but his constant buzzing

267
00:17:48,129 --> 00:17:49,881
is getting on my nerves.

268
00:17:50,632 --> 00:17:52,217
We need to swat this fly.

269
00:17:52,801 --> 00:17:54,344
You've done this before,
so you'll be good at it, right?

270
00:17:54,427 --> 00:17:56,554
No, this is
completely different from that.

271
00:17:56,638 --> 00:17:59,849
Before, I was tailing someone
connected to the case.

272
00:17:59,933 --> 00:18:02,977
But now you're asking me
to tail my own boss.

273
00:18:03,103 --> 00:18:04,312
It's not different at all.

274
00:18:04,396 --> 00:18:07,524
Our Chief Prosecutor
is deeply involved in this case.

275
00:18:07,649 --> 00:18:10,694
He's taking bribes from Han Gyeong-wook.

276
00:18:11,695 --> 00:18:14,072
Why are you telling me a secret like that?

277
00:18:14,656 --> 00:18:17,158
I'm just going to pretend
I didn't hear that.

278
00:18:17,242 --> 00:18:21,037
I just want to keep my head down
and have a long career. You get me?

279
00:18:21,121 --> 00:18:23,081
Chief Kim, wait.

280
00:18:23,206 --> 00:18:27,919
If you want that long career,
you have to cut that rotten lifeline.

281
00:18:28,002 --> 00:18:31,256
And make a new, sturdy,
and safe one for yourself.

282
00:18:31,756 --> 00:18:35,343
Don't you see what's at stake here?

283
00:18:36,761 --> 00:18:39,180
You'll approve my overtime, right?

284
00:18:40,098 --> 00:18:42,684
But what's Mr. Jeong thinking?

285
00:18:43,435 --> 00:18:44,602
He was so suspicious of him

286
00:18:44,686 --> 00:18:46,646
and now he wants us
to bring Bong Je-sun to the camper?

287
00:18:46,730 --> 00:18:49,107
Gosh, how am I supposed to know
what he's thinking?

288
00:18:49,691 --> 00:18:52,110
Oh, right. Was everything okay
on Mi-kyung's end?

289
00:18:52,193 --> 00:18:56,114
What's there to report?
Everything's quiet.

290
00:19:00,076 --> 00:19:01,411
- Hey.
- Hello.

291
00:19:01,536 --> 00:19:02,537
Hello.

292
00:19:06,416 --> 00:19:09,085
- What's that?
- Oh, this?

293
00:19:09,169 --> 00:19:11,546
You're working so hard
to help me get my memory back

294
00:19:11,629 --> 00:19:14,632
so I wanted to help out somehow
and brought a few things.

295
00:19:15,633 --> 00:19:16,801
You really overdo it.

296
00:19:17,510 --> 00:19:18,511
What?

297
00:19:21,973 --> 00:19:24,642
Hey, it's you, isn't it?
From the warehouse.

298
00:19:25,268 --> 00:19:27,729
- The warehouse?
- Yes. Don't you remember?

299
00:19:28,730 --> 00:19:32,317
You know, back when those
Heaven Capital goons dragged us away.

300
00:19:32,400 --> 00:19:34,360
Woof, woof!

301
00:19:34,444 --> 00:19:36,279
- Have you lost your mind?
- Are you trying to pick a fight?

302
00:19:36,362 --> 00:19:38,072
No, I'm not trying to pick a fight.

303
00:19:38,490 --> 00:19:40,575
I'm just glad you're okay.

304
00:19:40,658 --> 00:19:44,204
I was so worried
that you'd gotten seriously hurt.

305
00:19:44,496 --> 00:19:46,247
But you're tough, so you seem to be fine.

306
00:19:46,331 --> 00:19:49,292
Stop talking nonsense
and get in while I'm asking nicely.

307
00:19:49,375 --> 00:19:50,627
- Okay?
- Yes.

308
00:19:50,710 --> 00:19:52,754
Hurry. Let's go.

309
00:20:15,652 --> 00:20:18,655
Well, Chairman Hwang,
it's been a long time.

310
00:20:18,738 --> 00:20:20,782
You look even younger
than the last time I saw you.

311
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:25,954
Isn't that all thanks to you,
Deputy Director Han?

312
00:20:30,917 --> 00:20:33,461
You'll understand the business
once you see read that.

313
00:20:34,212 --> 00:20:37,173
I'll give you 10% of the profits
and give you my full support

314
00:20:37,590 --> 00:20:40,009
in rebuilding your organization.

315
00:20:40,093 --> 00:20:41,344
What do you say?

316
00:20:41,427 --> 00:20:45,181
I'd say that's
more than enough compensation

317
00:20:45,265 --> 00:20:46,599
for spending ten years in prison.

318
00:20:52,188 --> 00:20:55,149
You're not going to use some rat
like Yoo In-gu again

319
00:20:55,233 --> 00:20:58,194
- to stab me in the back, are you?
- Of course not.

320
00:20:59,195 --> 00:21:01,197
As long as the business goes well

321
00:21:01,489 --> 00:21:03,283
why would I have any reason
to do something like that?

322
00:21:07,453 --> 00:21:08,663
What is it?

323
00:21:08,746 --> 00:21:11,583
The reason you're giving me
such a good offer.

324
00:21:11,666 --> 00:21:13,585
You're as sharp as ever.

325
00:21:15,003 --> 00:21:18,423
There's something
I need you to do for me, Chairman Hwang.

326
00:21:29,100 --> 00:21:30,977
One of your men

327
00:21:31,102 --> 00:21:34,814
is in cahoots with that same
NIS agent from ten years ago.

328
00:21:35,565 --> 00:21:37,066
Did you know that?

329
00:21:37,817 --> 00:21:41,821
Those two have the missing package.

330
00:21:44,616 --> 00:21:47,285
So you're saying I should go to Beom-ryong

331
00:21:47,535 --> 00:21:49,579
get that package

332
00:21:50,246 --> 00:21:51,623
and bring it back?

333
00:21:52,498 --> 00:21:56,836
I know it's not easy to get
a runaway child to come back.

334
00:21:56,920 --> 00:21:58,671
If you can't do it, just say so.

335
00:21:58,755 --> 00:22:00,465
Whether by carrot or by stick

336
00:22:00,548 --> 00:22:03,259
all I have to do is bring him home, right?

337
00:22:04,802 --> 00:22:07,680
And recovering the package
shouldn't be too difficult either.

338
00:22:10,808 --> 00:22:12,685
Gosh, so I'm

339
00:22:13,144 --> 00:22:15,605
going into business
with Deputy Director Han.

340
00:22:24,656 --> 00:22:27,450
In return for this fine coffee,
let me give you a gift.

341
00:22:28,618 --> 00:22:31,412
Prosecutor Gang in this photo here

342
00:22:31,496 --> 00:22:33,206
came to see me a while ago.

343
00:22:33,957 --> 00:22:35,041
You...

344
00:22:35,917 --> 00:22:37,335
met with Prosecutor Gang?

345
00:22:37,418 --> 00:22:40,797
She said she would catch the real killer
in Director Kwon Soon-bok's murder case.

346
00:22:41,839 --> 00:22:43,675
I thought she was some kind of psycho

347
00:22:43,758 --> 00:22:45,677
but given the circumstances at the time

348
00:22:45,760 --> 00:22:48,304
I was desperate,
so I took her up on the offer.

349
00:22:48,388 --> 00:22:52,350
I even told Beom-ryong to meet with her.

350
00:22:53,142 --> 00:22:54,143
And?

351
00:22:54,227 --> 00:22:56,187
He never reported back on what happened

352
00:22:56,270 --> 00:22:58,940
so I just assumed it didn't work out
and gave up on it.

353
00:23:00,316 --> 00:23:02,819
But it looks like
things progressed this way.

354
00:23:02,986 --> 00:23:04,070
Right?

355
00:23:06,239 --> 00:23:07,740
Prosecutor Gang.

356
00:23:08,241 --> 00:23:12,328
She may have found out far more
about your shameful secrets

357
00:23:12,412 --> 00:23:15,289
than you might think.

358
00:23:18,209 --> 00:23:19,544
Joong-gi.

359
00:23:20,253 --> 00:23:24,090
We're not far from the finish line.
You know that, right?

360
00:23:24,173 --> 00:23:26,384
- Yes.
- But...

361
00:23:26,968 --> 00:23:29,554
At a time when we should be
making our final push

362
00:23:29,887 --> 00:23:32,890
why do stumbling blocks
like Jeong Ho-myeong or Prosecutor Gang

363
00:23:32,974 --> 00:23:34,517
keep popping up?

364
00:23:35,018 --> 00:23:36,310
I'm sure

365
00:23:36,686 --> 00:23:39,897
I instructed you to clear the path.

366
00:23:40,690 --> 00:23:41,691
I'm sorry.

367
00:23:49,323 --> 00:23:52,243
Before that woman becomes
an even bigger headache

368
00:23:52,326 --> 00:23:54,454
you take care of it on your end.

369
00:23:56,039 --> 00:23:57,790
I'll take care of it
as quickly as possible.

370
00:24:34,035 --> 00:24:35,244
What is it?

371
00:24:35,328 --> 00:24:37,330
What did you drag us out here
to talk about?

372
00:24:37,413 --> 00:24:39,415
Weren't you just complaining
about how this guy is not to be trusted?

373
00:24:39,499 --> 00:24:41,292
Hey, you go on inside.

374
00:24:41,375 --> 00:24:43,294
- What?
- What?

375
00:24:44,587 --> 00:24:47,048
I said go on ahead.
The three of us need to talk.

376
00:24:47,215 --> 00:24:48,382
Okay.

377
00:24:51,094 --> 00:24:53,554
- Go where--
- Where else? Can't you see the door?

378
00:24:53,638 --> 00:24:54,972
Want to jump in the water instead?

379
00:24:55,973 --> 00:24:57,934
I'll be in there, then.

380
00:25:00,144 --> 00:25:01,229
Man, those must be heavy.

381
00:25:23,334 --> 00:25:24,418
You guys.

382
00:25:25,169 --> 00:25:26,587
Now, don't freak out.

383
00:25:30,341 --> 00:25:31,342
Are you serious?

384
00:25:31,425 --> 00:25:33,136
You're saying Han Gyeong-wook
knew everything?

385
00:25:33,219 --> 00:25:34,345
Yes.

386
00:25:35,138 --> 00:25:37,014
He probably thinks we have the package.

387
00:25:37,431 --> 00:25:39,267
I think he'll be back soon.

388
00:25:39,350 --> 00:25:40,893
Well, then we can just
keep pretending we have it.

389
00:25:40,977 --> 00:25:42,186
That won't last long.

390
00:25:42,270 --> 00:25:44,522
He'll catch on quick.
You know what he's like.

391
00:25:45,356 --> 00:25:46,607
Before that happens

392
00:25:46,691 --> 00:25:49,360
we need to find some kind of evidence
of Han Gyeong-wook's wrongdoings

393
00:25:49,443 --> 00:25:50,444
and strike first.

394
00:25:50,528 --> 00:25:52,613
But we don't have much time.
Is that even possible?

395
00:25:52,697 --> 00:25:54,240
We have to try.

396
00:25:54,323 --> 00:25:55,867
If we want to find out quickly

397
00:25:56,200 --> 00:25:58,870
we'll have to dig
into Heaven Capital or Heaven Casino.

398
00:25:59,328 --> 00:26:03,499
But the casino's system
makes it hard to infiltrate.

399
00:26:03,583 --> 00:26:05,209
However, the Heaven Capital business
seems possible.

400
00:26:06,043 --> 00:26:08,921
After Yoo In-gu stepped down

401
00:26:09,005 --> 00:26:11,299
Chairman Do
and that guy, Geum Kang-sik, took over.

402
00:26:14,385 --> 00:26:16,804
- Kang-sik is in charge?
- You know him?

403
00:26:18,890 --> 00:26:20,099
We know him, but...

404
00:26:21,058 --> 00:26:23,311
We're too embarrassed to even admit we do.

405
00:26:25,271 --> 00:26:26,272
Yes, sir.

406
00:26:27,190 --> 00:26:28,774
Kang-sik, the shoes.

407
00:26:31,235 --> 00:26:32,278
Yes, sir.

408
00:26:33,696 --> 00:26:34,697
Here, sir.

409
00:26:45,208 --> 00:26:47,543
- Thank you.
- When we were in the Hwasan Sect

410
00:26:47,627 --> 00:26:49,253
he just shined my shoes.

411
00:26:49,587 --> 00:26:51,547
He was really good
at shining shoes, though.

412
00:26:51,839 --> 00:26:54,508
But he couldn't even manage
a single food stall properly

413
00:26:54,592 --> 00:26:56,260
so he was the epitome of incompetence.

414
00:26:57,136 --> 00:26:58,346
Perfect.

415
00:26:58,429 --> 00:27:01,933
When an incompetent guy takes charge,
things are bound to fall apart.

416
00:27:02,850 --> 00:27:04,936
If we can just squeeze Geum Kang-sik

417
00:27:05,019 --> 00:27:07,647
we can find evidence
that Han ordered the money collection

418
00:27:07,730 --> 00:27:10,358
or find a trail
of where the illegal funds went.

419
00:27:11,275 --> 00:27:13,486
What's so hard about
shaking down Kang-sik?

420
00:27:14,028 --> 00:27:17,198
- Let's do it now.
- You can dismiss Geum Kang-sik

421
00:27:17,365 --> 00:27:18,699
but he's got the other boys.

422
00:27:18,783 --> 00:27:22,119
And he saw what happened to Yoo In-gu,
so he's probably being extremely cautious.

423
00:27:23,537 --> 00:27:27,625
I'm sure he is.
That's why that will be our Plan B.

424
00:27:28,042 --> 00:27:31,879
We have a much more certain way
to take down Han Gyeong-wook.

425
00:27:31,963 --> 00:27:34,048
A more certain way? What is it?

426
00:27:37,885 --> 00:27:40,846
We just have to make Bulgae talk
and get the package.

427
00:27:40,930 --> 00:27:42,598
Are you kidding me?

428
00:27:42,682 --> 00:27:44,850
He says he can't remember anything.
How are you supposed to make him talk?

429
00:27:44,934 --> 00:27:47,395
How many times do I have to tell you?
It's all an act.

430
00:27:49,397 --> 00:27:51,065
Hey, look at him.

431
00:27:51,774 --> 00:27:53,985
Does he really look like Bulgae to you?

432
00:27:54,068 --> 00:27:59,448
Hey, at that K-pop dance place yesterday,
he was living like a total slave.

433
00:27:59,532 --> 00:28:01,701
If he were Bulgae,
why would he live like that?

434
00:28:01,909 --> 00:28:04,203
I also think you've got it wrong.

435
00:28:05,454 --> 00:28:08,541
Do you have any idea how many spies
I dealt with at the NIS?

436
00:28:09,000 --> 00:28:10,459
An act like that...

437
00:28:11,502 --> 00:28:13,921
I just know it when I see it.

438
00:28:15,423 --> 00:28:17,633
You're telling me that
dopey look on his face is all an act?

439
00:28:17,717 --> 00:28:18,926
Just you watch.

440
00:28:19,010 --> 00:28:22,847
I'm going to rip that
detestable Bong Je-sun mask right off him.

441
00:28:27,435 --> 00:28:29,353
He keeps staring over here.

442
00:28:29,437 --> 00:28:30,563
So they think this is funny?

443
00:28:31,564 --> 00:28:33,065
Look at them, having a blast.

444
00:29:15,232 --> 00:29:16,609
Oh, my stomach.

445
00:29:17,568 --> 00:29:18,736
Are you all done talking?

446
00:29:18,819 --> 00:29:20,363
Of course. Why else would we come in?

447
00:29:20,863 --> 00:29:23,449
- Have you made your decision?
- What decision?

448
00:29:24,533 --> 00:29:26,744
Whether you're going to tell the truth now

449
00:29:26,827 --> 00:29:29,372
or keep pretending to be Bong Je-sun.

450
00:29:29,455 --> 00:29:30,623
It's time to decide.

451
00:29:31,582 --> 00:29:35,086
Mr Jeong, just as you're saying

452
00:29:35,169 --> 00:29:38,339
I wish this amnesia were just an act.
I really do.

453
00:29:38,422 --> 00:29:40,758
But I'm telling you,
I really don't remember a thing.

454
00:29:42,093 --> 00:29:43,135
Is that so?

455
00:29:44,095 --> 00:29:45,554
Then let me explain it to you.

456
00:29:45,638 --> 00:29:46,931
What?

457
00:29:47,348 --> 00:29:50,518
Agent Bulgae of the Ministry
of People's Armed Forces.

458
00:29:51,268 --> 00:29:53,604
Dispatched to the South and overseas
for secret operations.

459
00:29:53,687 --> 00:29:57,400
A human weapon trained in North Korea
for various special missions.

460
00:29:57,858 --> 00:30:01,821
Rumored to be a master of disguise
and a Taekkyeon expert.

461
00:30:01,904 --> 00:30:05,616
A legendary spy whose identity
has never been compromised.

462
00:30:06,325 --> 00:30:09,620
A guy like that gets amnesia

463
00:30:09,703 --> 00:30:12,123
and holes up in South Korea for ten years?

464
00:30:13,582 --> 00:30:15,459
Does that make any sense to you?

465
00:30:20,256 --> 00:30:24,135
Believe it or not, it's the truth.

466
00:30:26,887 --> 00:30:28,931
So you're going to stick to that story?

467
00:30:31,016 --> 00:30:32,601
Then I have no choice.

468
00:30:34,019 --> 00:30:37,690
I'll just have to make sure.

469
00:30:38,399 --> 00:30:40,776
Hey, what are you going to do
to make sure?

470
00:30:41,777 --> 00:30:43,028
Watch out!

471
00:31:04,341 --> 00:31:05,926
- Darn.
- Darn it.

472
00:31:07,595 --> 00:31:08,679
What was that?

473
00:31:10,222 --> 00:31:12,141
- What?
- Did you all see that?

474
00:31:12,224 --> 00:31:13,517
You think Bong Je-sun
could have dodged that?

475
00:31:13,601 --> 00:31:15,811
Are you crazy? What if you'd hit him?

476
00:31:15,895 --> 00:31:18,147
Hey, is he a target?
Why do you keep throwing things?

477
00:31:18,230 --> 00:31:19,231
You almost killed him!

478
00:31:19,315 --> 00:31:21,400
I knew he'd dodge it. Because he's Bulgae.

479
00:31:21,484 --> 00:31:22,776
Are you okay?

480
00:31:24,069 --> 00:31:26,363
I don't even know how I dodged that.
I was so shocked.

481
00:31:26,447 --> 00:31:27,990
I barely ducked
my head like this, but right here...

482
00:31:28,073 --> 00:31:29,325
Gosh, it stings.

483
00:31:29,408 --> 00:31:31,452
It's bleeding. I'm bleeding.

484
00:31:31,952 --> 00:31:34,622
- I'm bleeding. Blood!
- What? You punk...

485
00:31:34,747 --> 00:31:36,248
Hey! If you don't want a hole in your head

486
00:31:36,332 --> 00:31:38,876
reveal your identity
and tell me where the package is!

487
00:31:38,959 --> 00:31:41,629
- Mr. Jeong, please stop.
- Yes, you're way too worked up.

488
00:31:41,754 --> 00:31:44,965
So, just because I dodged that,
I'm Bulgae?

489
00:31:45,049 --> 00:31:47,384
Hey, look. You dodged it. See?

490
00:31:47,468 --> 00:31:49,762
He dodged it. He must be Bulgae, right?

491
00:31:50,471 --> 00:31:52,973
Why didn't you dodge this? Why not?

492
00:31:53,390 --> 00:31:54,725
You're calling me Bulgae

493
00:31:54,808 --> 00:31:56,310
for dodging something
most people would dodge?

494
00:31:56,560 --> 00:31:58,229
You've really gone too far. Darn it.

495
00:31:58,479 --> 00:32:01,315
I put up with the soda can. But...

496
00:32:01,732 --> 00:32:03,400
But you throw a knife at a person?

497
00:32:03,567 --> 00:32:06,278
What if I hadn't dodged it?
It came right at me.

498
00:32:07,029 --> 00:32:08,447
Bulgae, my foot.

499
00:32:08,531 --> 00:32:10,866
You can say it a hundred times,
but I still don't remember a thing.

500
00:32:10,950 --> 00:32:14,828
What makes you think I'm acting?
You keep spouting nonsense.

501
00:32:15,162 --> 00:32:17,248
Because none of it makes sense!

502
00:32:17,331 --> 00:32:19,333
For ten years,
with no friends and no girlfriend

503
00:32:19,416 --> 00:32:21,710
you put up with all the crap
at that small company

504
00:32:21,794 --> 00:32:22,920
and spent all your time

505
00:32:23,003 --> 00:32:25,464
looking after
that troublemaker nephew? Why?

506
00:32:25,798 --> 00:32:29,426
If it wasn't an act you'd have
no reason to live like that. Right?

507
00:32:29,510 --> 00:32:32,930
An act? You call this an act?
You think I enjoy living like this?

508
00:32:36,141 --> 00:32:38,060
You think I enjoy any of this?

509
00:32:45,359 --> 00:32:47,403
Nam-il is the only family I have

510
00:32:48,279 --> 00:32:50,656
and I don't even remember
who I used to be.

511
00:32:50,739 --> 00:32:52,741
Do you think it's easy
to get close to people?

512
00:32:53,158 --> 00:32:55,995
The second someone asks
where I'm from, I'm speechless.

513
00:32:56,704 --> 00:32:58,622
The small company? The power trips?

514
00:32:59,582 --> 00:33:01,375
You think anyone enjoys
putting up with that?

515
00:33:02,668 --> 00:33:04,670
At my age, I have no skills
and nowhere else to go.

516
00:33:05,546 --> 00:33:07,172
I'm telling you,
I have nowhere else to go.

517
00:33:11,468 --> 00:33:13,554
Honestly, doesn't he have a point?

518
00:33:13,637 --> 00:33:16,932
What makes you think
Bong Je-sun can just get another job?

519
00:33:17,474 --> 00:33:19,059
I feel the same way.

520
00:33:21,437 --> 00:33:24,189
He said he hasn't dated once
in ten years. How pathetic.

521
00:33:24,523 --> 00:33:26,817
And just look at him.
Who would ever like that face?

522
00:33:28,110 --> 00:33:30,946
And accusing him of being a spy
just because he's unpopular

523
00:33:31,030 --> 00:33:34,033
that just makes us as pathetic as him.

524
00:33:40,539 --> 00:33:41,540
You.

525
00:33:43,751 --> 00:33:45,085
You really...

526
00:33:47,129 --> 00:33:48,380
I've had enough.

527
00:33:49,423 --> 00:33:51,050
- Tie him up.
- What?

528
00:33:51,759 --> 00:33:52,760
Who's he talking about?

529
00:33:52,843 --> 00:33:54,511
Let's just talk this out.

530
00:33:54,595 --> 00:33:55,596
Talk?

531
00:33:56,221 --> 00:33:58,265
Don't you realize what it means
that Han Gyeong-wook came to see me?

532
00:33:58,557 --> 00:33:59,725
You guys...

533
00:33:59,850 --> 00:34:01,935
You saw the Hwasan Sect
get destroyed firsthand.

534
00:34:03,103 --> 00:34:04,938
You want to be careless
and go through the same thing again?

535
00:34:12,863 --> 00:34:14,281
- Are you okay?
- Yes. Gosh!

536
00:34:14,365 --> 00:34:15,616
Does it hurt a lot?

537
00:34:18,661 --> 00:34:19,828
So, what are you going to do?

538
00:34:20,287 --> 00:34:21,372
You're not going to do
anything crazy, are you?

539
00:34:22,122 --> 00:34:24,583
Oh no. That's... that's the truth serum.

540
00:34:25,209 --> 00:34:26,377
Truth serum?

541
00:34:27,127 --> 00:34:29,004
It's a drug used by the CIA.

542
00:34:29,088 --> 00:34:31,965
Once you're injected,
you'll tell the truth within ten minutes

543
00:34:32,049 --> 00:34:34,885
but there's a 50% chance
you'll spend your life drooling.

544
00:34:34,968 --> 00:34:36,261
It's a deadly poison.

545
00:34:36,387 --> 00:34:38,472
I didn't want to resort to this

546
00:34:38,972 --> 00:34:41,350
but if you're going to keep this up,
I have no choice.

547
00:34:42,351 --> 00:34:44,353
- You're kidding, right?
- I'm serious.

548
00:34:44,436 --> 00:34:46,939
- Darn it.
- Hey, Jeong Ho-myeong.

549
00:34:47,022 --> 00:34:48,732
Now you're resorting to drugs?

550
00:34:48,816 --> 00:34:50,651
Are you human? Are you serious?

551
00:34:50,734 --> 00:34:52,361
Shut it, you thug.

552
00:34:59,368 --> 00:35:00,494
Bulgae.

553
00:35:01,120 --> 00:35:03,038
This is your last chance. Think carefully.

554
00:35:03,122 --> 00:35:04,873
I'm not doing this
because of a personal grudge.

555
00:35:04,957 --> 00:35:06,709
If you keep lying,
the people of Yeongseon Island

556
00:35:06,792 --> 00:35:08,460
the dance club members,
your nephew Heo Nam-il

557
00:35:08,585 --> 00:35:10,045
and Prosecutor Gang will all be in danger.

558
00:35:10,838 --> 00:35:13,924
So just tell me now. It's not too late.

559
00:35:22,433 --> 00:35:24,893
You seriously think
that'll bring back my memories?

560
00:35:25,477 --> 00:35:27,563
What are you all doing?
Have you all gone insane?

561
00:35:27,855 --> 00:35:29,690
Are you just going to
stand there and watch?

562
00:35:30,232 --> 00:35:33,235
That was your last chance. So be it.

563
00:35:33,902 --> 00:35:37,197
Take one more step
and this thug will beat you up.

564
00:35:37,322 --> 00:35:40,242
- Two steps, three steps, four steps.
- No!

565
00:35:40,325 --> 00:35:41,994
Let go of me!

566
00:35:44,413 --> 00:35:46,123
Wait!

567
00:35:50,210 --> 00:35:51,211
Let go of me.

568
00:35:51,295 --> 00:35:54,089
You're out of your mind. Stop!

569
00:35:54,173 --> 00:35:56,800
I said let go!
You know I hate being touched, right?

570
00:35:56,884 --> 00:35:59,720
- Are you with the NIS or the CIA?
- Do you even know what CIA is?

571
00:35:59,803 --> 00:36:01,638
- This is dangerous!
- Do you know the CIA, you punk?

572
00:36:01,722 --> 00:36:03,223
- Stop it!
- You lunatic!

573
00:36:03,307 --> 00:36:05,684
- Let go of me, you punk!
- It's too dangerous!

574
00:36:05,768 --> 00:36:07,352
Stop!

575
00:36:12,483 --> 00:36:13,567
Do it.

576
00:36:14,860 --> 00:36:16,069
What?

577
00:36:16,153 --> 00:36:18,322
Just inject me with that syringe.

578
00:36:19,698 --> 00:36:21,658
No matter how many times I tell you
I've lost my memory

579
00:36:22,075 --> 00:36:24,077
you have no intention of listening.

580
00:36:24,161 --> 00:36:25,913
Throwing knives at people

581
00:36:25,996 --> 00:36:27,831
and threatening them with your crude talk.

582
00:36:27,915 --> 00:36:29,208
What you guys are doing right now...

583
00:36:29,291 --> 00:36:32,544
How is this any different
from what that Han Gyeong-wook guy does?

584
00:36:33,670 --> 00:36:36,131
You might as well just inject me.

585
00:36:37,841 --> 00:36:39,092
Inject me and...

586
00:36:40,469 --> 00:36:43,597
Yes, go on and hear
what this so-called truth is.

587
00:36:45,224 --> 00:36:47,059
Just do it. Inject me.

588
00:36:55,108 --> 00:36:58,862
- Mr. Jeong!
- Do you still want to go through with it?

589
00:37:06,537 --> 00:37:08,872
Look me straight in the eye.

590
00:37:14,628 --> 00:37:15,879
You really...

591
00:37:16,547 --> 00:37:18,465
don't have a single memory as Bulgae?

592
00:37:20,467 --> 00:37:23,387
I told you.
How many times do I have to say it?

593
00:37:23,804 --> 00:37:26,557
How many darn times do I have to tell you?

594
00:37:26,640 --> 00:37:28,684
I don't remember.

595
00:37:28,767 --> 00:37:30,644
So why are you calling me a liar?

596
00:37:31,895 --> 00:37:33,564
- Hey, Gong-bok. Here.
- Okay.

597
00:37:33,730 --> 00:37:34,898
That's enough.

598
00:37:36,608 --> 00:37:38,235
Keep it up. You're doing great.

599
00:37:38,318 --> 00:37:41,488
- You idiot.
- Just stop it already.

600
00:37:49,121 --> 00:37:50,205
Fine.

601
00:37:50,873 --> 00:37:52,583
Well, if he still denies it after all this

602
00:37:54,042 --> 00:37:57,379
- I guess that's true.
- Yes. Mr. Jeong Ho-myeong.

603
00:37:58,964 --> 00:38:00,257
- Are you okay?
- Yes, I'm fine.

604
00:38:00,340 --> 00:38:01,800
- Does it hurt a lot?
- Yes.

605
00:38:05,220 --> 00:38:08,348
Oh, and that shot from before?
It was this.

606
00:38:09,349 --> 00:38:11,268
- What?
- What did you say, you fool?

607
00:38:12,436 --> 00:38:14,563
Hey, Bulgae. No, Bong Je-sun.

608
00:38:14,646 --> 00:38:15,647
My bad.

609
00:38:16,315 --> 00:38:18,609
You're a good guy, so you'll understand.

610
00:38:22,237 --> 00:38:23,488
Darn it, seriously.

611
00:38:25,449 --> 00:38:27,242
- Are you okay?
- Thanks for saving me.

612
00:38:27,326 --> 00:38:28,869
- Untie him, quick.
- Oh, yes.

613
00:38:28,952 --> 00:38:30,829
That darn devil, Jeong Ho-myeong.

614
00:38:35,709 --> 00:38:37,294
He tied this really tight.

615
00:38:38,211 --> 00:38:40,547
A master of disguise
and a Taekkyeon expert...

616
00:38:42,925 --> 00:38:45,093
Okay, let's think about this.

617
00:38:45,802 --> 00:38:49,348
This guy who's some kind of
martial arts master or whatever

618
00:38:49,723 --> 00:38:52,267
seems to be a trained North Korean spy.

619
00:38:52,351 --> 00:38:55,896
The other is Gang Beom-ryong,
the former number two of the Hwasan Sect.

620
00:38:55,979 --> 00:38:57,230
And the last one

621
00:38:57,314 --> 00:39:01,151
is some agent from the NIS
who knows Han Gyeong-wook well.

622
00:39:02,986 --> 00:39:04,988
What kind of combination is this?

623
00:39:05,072 --> 00:39:07,199
What kind of scheme are they plotting

624
00:39:07,282 --> 00:39:08,825
that brought these three together?

625
00:39:10,285 --> 00:39:11,870
A North Korean spy

626
00:39:12,955 --> 00:39:16,416
the National Intelligence Service,
and Gang Beom-ryong.

627
00:39:18,919 --> 00:39:22,005
Oh, now that you mention it, ten years ago

628
00:39:22,297 --> 00:39:25,384
Deputy Director Han
came to see Chairman Hwang.

629
00:39:25,467 --> 00:39:27,219
He wanted to work together on a job.

630
00:39:27,302 --> 00:39:28,470
A job?

631
00:39:28,553 --> 00:39:31,473
He asked us to find him
a solid guy back then.

632
00:39:31,932 --> 00:39:35,060
I remember Gang Beom-ryong
and Ma Gong-bok were assigned to it.

633
00:39:36,728 --> 00:39:37,771
So...

634
00:39:38,647 --> 00:39:41,024
- they acted on an order?
- Yes.

635
00:39:41,525 --> 00:39:44,486
- So, what happened with that job?
- Well...

636
00:39:45,070 --> 00:39:47,906
Right after that job, Deputy Director Han

637
00:39:48,490 --> 00:39:51,118
and Yoo In-gu teamed up
and backstabbed the chairman.

638
00:39:51,201 --> 00:39:53,412
So whether they succeeded or what...

639
00:39:53,495 --> 00:39:55,247
I don't really know that part.

640
00:39:55,330 --> 00:39:59,209
I bet that order was the ferry case.

641
00:39:59,292 --> 00:40:01,294
And that must be when those three

642
00:40:01,378 --> 00:40:03,296
and Deputy Director Han
got involved with each other.

643
00:40:03,714 --> 00:40:07,634
Considering how Han Gyeong-wook
is still paying special attention to this

644
00:40:07,718 --> 00:40:09,720
it seems like something major

645
00:40:09,803 --> 00:40:12,305
must have happened on that ferry.

646
00:40:13,557 --> 00:40:16,309
Darn, what could it be?

647
00:40:18,103 --> 00:40:20,939
Mr. Nam, you said you had
a contact at the NIS, right?

648
00:40:21,023 --> 00:40:22,149
- Yes.
- Okay.

649
00:40:22,232 --> 00:40:23,942
Then can you find out

650
00:40:24,026 --> 00:40:25,569
what happened ten years ago

651
00:40:25,652 --> 00:40:27,612
- about this ferry case?
- Yes.

652
00:40:30,449 --> 00:40:31,491
What?

653
00:40:32,451 --> 00:40:33,493
It's Secretary Baek.

654
00:40:36,872 --> 00:40:38,707
- Yes?
- Chairman Do.

655
00:40:38,790 --> 00:40:40,500
You haven't forgotten
tomorrow's delivery, have you?

656
00:40:40,584 --> 00:40:41,752
Of course not.

657
00:40:42,461 --> 00:40:43,545
But what about it?

658
00:40:43,628 --> 00:40:45,464
The Deputy Director says
he has something to tell you

659
00:40:45,714 --> 00:40:46,882
and asks you to come in today.

660
00:40:46,965 --> 00:40:50,302
Today? Yes, understood.

661
00:40:52,596 --> 00:40:54,181
Something to tell me?

662
00:40:55,348 --> 00:40:57,893
What a roundabout way
of telling me to hurry up with the money.

663
00:40:58,310 --> 00:41:01,354
Mr. Nam, go to Mr. Geum's Capital
and get the bag.

664
00:41:01,730 --> 00:41:03,690
What? The bag?

665
00:41:29,841 --> 00:41:31,134
It's a green juice.

666
00:41:31,593 --> 00:41:34,387
It's said to help with fatigue
and clear your head.

667
00:41:34,471 --> 00:41:35,889
Here, drink this.

668
00:41:41,269 --> 00:41:42,562
Fine, don't drink it.

669
00:41:42,646 --> 00:41:44,439
It's not like I'm giving it to you
because I like you.

670
00:41:58,578 --> 00:42:00,330
I'm sorry.

671
00:42:01,414 --> 00:42:05,085
For being just Bong Je-sun
and not the human weapon, Bulgae.

672
00:42:06,628 --> 00:42:08,130
You know

673
00:42:08,255 --> 00:42:10,340
I don't think I've ever felt

674
00:42:11,258 --> 00:42:14,302
as frustrated about my amnesia
as I do today.

675
00:42:15,679 --> 00:42:19,474
The people on Yeongseon Island
and Nam-il could all be in danger.

676
00:42:20,934 --> 00:42:24,229
I'm sure there's a clue
in my memories that could save them

677
00:42:24,855 --> 00:42:26,731
so why did I forget everything?

678
00:42:27,566 --> 00:42:29,651
I can't even remember the faintest detail.

679
00:42:35,615 --> 00:42:38,660
It's not that
I don't understand you, Mr. Jeong.

680
00:42:39,244 --> 00:42:42,664
If there's any other way I can help,
please tell me.

681
00:42:42,831 --> 00:42:45,834
Then I'll do anything. Anything.

682
00:42:51,173 --> 00:42:52,591
Well, isn't this lovely?

683
00:42:54,426 --> 00:42:55,969
Hey, you guys stay here.

684
00:42:56,803 --> 00:42:59,806
- Why? Are you going somewhere?
- Finding the package is a lost cause.

685
00:42:59,973 --> 00:43:02,851
I have to go with Plan B
I mentioned earlier.

686
00:43:03,476 --> 00:43:05,312
I'll head over to Heaven Capital

687
00:43:05,395 --> 00:43:07,522
so you guys stay here
and work with Bulgae...

688
00:43:10,400 --> 00:43:11,401
I mean work with Bong Je-sun

689
00:43:11,484 --> 00:43:14,029
and make a list of places
where the package could be.

690
00:43:14,154 --> 00:43:15,447
Places where the package could be?

691
00:43:15,530 --> 00:43:19,576
Every single place Bong Je-sun went to
while he lived on Yeongseon Island.

692
00:43:20,994 --> 00:43:22,537
Starting tomorrow,
we'll split into two teams.

693
00:43:22,621 --> 00:43:24,164
One team will take Heaven Capital

694
00:43:24,247 --> 00:43:26,333
and the other team will take the receiver

695
00:43:26,416 --> 00:43:27,959
and comb through Yeongseon Island.

696
00:43:28,043 --> 00:43:29,127
You never know.

697
00:43:29,211 --> 00:43:30,545
We might find something.

698
00:43:32,172 --> 00:43:34,507
- Okay.
- You can help with that, right?

699
00:43:34,591 --> 00:43:36,468
Yes, I'll do it.

700
00:43:38,637 --> 00:43:41,348
Open the cabinet next to the bed.
The receiver should be in there.

701
00:44:10,627 --> 00:44:12,837
Things are a little tight this month.

702
00:44:12,921 --> 00:44:15,799
I have to pay my guys too.
Just one more month.

703
00:44:16,716 --> 00:44:17,759
Give me an extension.

704
00:44:17,842 --> 00:44:19,928
You know perfectly well
that laundry payments

705
00:44:20,011 --> 00:44:21,346
have to be delivered on time.

706
00:44:22,055 --> 00:44:25,308
- You didn't know?
- I know. But...

707
00:44:25,392 --> 00:44:27,310
Come on, just help me out this once.

708
00:44:27,394 --> 00:44:29,604
These are Deputy Director Han's orders.

709
00:44:30,105 --> 00:44:32,482
Our hands are tied, you get me?

710
00:44:33,024 --> 00:44:35,235
See you around, President Geum.

711
00:44:48,039 --> 00:44:49,124
Boss.

712
00:44:50,292 --> 00:44:53,878
Did they really take everything?
The guys are really unhappy.

713
00:44:54,129 --> 00:44:56,256
At least when Yoo In-gu was around,
our paychecks were never late.

714
00:44:56,423 --> 00:44:57,549
Everyone's saying
the old days were better.

715
00:45:01,469 --> 00:45:03,638
What are you looking at, you punks?
Get to work!

716
00:45:04,764 --> 00:45:07,058
What? Yoo In-gu?

717
00:45:08,727 --> 00:45:10,854
Which one of you bastards
said that crap? Damn it.

718
00:45:12,272 --> 00:45:13,440
Hey.

719
00:45:13,898 --> 00:45:16,943
Who do you think saved this organization
after Yoo In-gu nearly destroyed it?

720
00:45:17,027 --> 00:45:18,445
The organization is struggling

721
00:45:18,528 --> 00:45:21,031
and you're driving around
in a nice car by yourself.

722
00:45:21,156 --> 00:45:23,491
The guys only say that
because it's what they see.

723
00:45:26,119 --> 00:45:28,997
Hey, I take the bus
just to save money on gas.

724
00:45:29,581 --> 00:45:32,459
Not me. It was the other guys.

725
00:45:32,542 --> 00:45:33,543
Whatever. Forget it.

726
00:45:35,920 --> 00:45:38,423
Hey, just keep the guys in line.

727
00:45:38,631 --> 00:45:40,717
I'll figure out a way
to get them paid. Got it?

728
00:45:40,800 --> 00:45:43,595
- Yes, Boss.
- Get out of here. Go away.

729
00:45:54,689 --> 00:45:56,024
You're right on time.

730
00:45:57,025 --> 00:45:59,861
Chairman Hwang,
this is Chairman Do Hyeon-tae.

731
00:46:00,070 --> 00:46:03,073
Chairman Do,
this is Chairman Hwang Hwa-san.

732
00:46:04,240 --> 00:46:06,242
I'm Hwang Hwa-san, Chairman Do.

733
00:46:06,326 --> 00:46:07,327
I'm Do Hyeon-tae.

734
00:46:07,744 --> 00:46:11,331
Could you be from the Hwasan Sect?

735
00:46:11,414 --> 00:46:12,582
Oh, my.

736
00:46:12,916 --> 00:46:16,211
For someone like you
to recognize an old man like me.

737
00:46:16,628 --> 00:46:17,796
I'm honored.

738
00:46:19,005 --> 00:46:20,256
Not at all.

739
00:46:20,590 --> 00:46:22,217
- Please, have a seat.
- Yes.

740
00:46:29,391 --> 00:46:30,433
We'll register Chairman Hwang

741
00:46:30,517 --> 00:46:32,894
as a director
of Yeongseon Future Development

742
00:46:32,977 --> 00:46:35,522
and he'll be in charge of
the Heaven Capital business from now on.

743
00:46:37,107 --> 00:46:39,734
But we've been handling that
just fine on our end.

744
00:46:40,276 --> 00:46:42,612
Why go through all the trouble?
We could just...

745
00:46:42,695 --> 00:46:44,823
Chairman Do,
you have way too much on your plate

746
00:46:44,906 --> 00:46:47,742
with the hotel, casino,
and the Yeongseon Island project.

747
00:46:47,826 --> 00:46:49,411
We need to be efficient.

748
00:46:49,494 --> 00:46:51,746
Think of it as going back
to how things were under Yoo In-gu.

749
00:46:54,666 --> 00:46:56,376
How things were under Yoo In-gu?

750
00:46:56,876 --> 00:46:57,919
Oh, and...

751
00:46:58,628 --> 00:47:03,216
Let's wrap up the case
you were following as well.

752
00:47:03,967 --> 00:47:06,511
That kind of work
is Chairman Hwang's specialty, after all.

753
00:47:12,559 --> 00:47:13,601
Understood.

754
00:47:14,602 --> 00:47:17,021
Having you here, Chairman,
takes a huge weight off my shoulders.

755
00:47:17,147 --> 00:47:21,359
From now on, if you run into any trouble,
just say the word.

756
00:47:22,026 --> 00:47:23,945
We're on the same team now, after all.

757
00:47:24,028 --> 00:47:27,699
I'll give it my all. I'm here to help.

758
00:47:27,782 --> 00:47:29,868
Thank you.
I look forward to learning from you.

759
00:47:29,951 --> 00:47:31,244
Of course.

760
00:47:42,839 --> 00:47:45,008
He thinks he can sideline me

761
00:47:45,091 --> 00:47:46,885
by putting some washed-up
old geezer in charge?

762
00:47:47,302 --> 00:47:50,305
I do all the hard work,
and that guy reaps the benefits.

763
00:47:52,557 --> 00:47:54,559
What do you think, Mr. Nam?

764
00:47:54,642 --> 00:47:56,394
I believe we need to take action.

765
00:47:57,145 --> 00:48:00,231
If profits from Heaven Capital
start dropping tomorrow

766
00:48:00,815 --> 00:48:02,275
it'll disrupt our cash flow.

767
00:48:02,358 --> 00:48:05,361
It's not just about the money.

768
00:48:05,445 --> 00:48:07,280
I have a really bad feeling about this.

769
00:48:07,363 --> 00:48:09,365
No matter how I look at it,
this is a signal from Deputy Director Han

770
00:48:09,449 --> 00:48:10,658
that he doesn't trust me.

771
00:48:10,992 --> 00:48:13,786
If I just sit back,
I'll end up just like Yoo In-gu.

772
00:48:13,870 --> 00:48:15,997
Surely Deputy Director Han
wouldn't do that, would he?

773
00:48:16,080 --> 00:48:17,874
I know Han Gyeong-wook very well.

774
00:48:19,667 --> 00:48:21,753
Keep the hitmen on standby.

775
00:48:23,421 --> 00:48:26,799
And if you find even the smallest lead
on Deputy Director Han

776
00:48:27,091 --> 00:48:29,344
tell them to contact me right away.

777
00:48:29,427 --> 00:48:30,428
Yes, sir.

778
00:48:35,767 --> 00:48:37,560
Hey, it's an emergency.

779
00:48:37,644 --> 00:48:39,521
I said I'd pay you back right away!

780
00:48:40,021 --> 00:48:41,064
Hey, hold on.

781
00:48:43,733 --> 00:48:45,318
What's going on?

782
00:48:59,582 --> 00:49:01,834
Long time no see, kid.

783
00:49:03,086 --> 00:49:04,420
Boss!

784
00:49:12,220 --> 00:49:13,930
President Geum Kang-sik.

785
00:49:14,514 --> 00:49:16,766
Live long enough and you see everything.

786
00:49:16,849 --> 00:49:18,226
Both you and Yoo In-gu...

787
00:49:18,309 --> 00:49:20,937
Punks like you being called President?

788
00:49:21,938 --> 00:49:25,608
What has this world come to?

789
00:49:25,692 --> 00:49:26,693
Oh, yes.

790
00:49:27,235 --> 00:49:28,903
Aren't you supposed to be in jail?

791
00:49:28,987 --> 00:49:32,740
Why? You got a problem with me being out?

792
00:49:32,824 --> 00:49:36,035
What? No.
That's not what I meant. Not at all.

793
00:49:38,037 --> 00:49:39,998
- Kang-sik.
- Yes, Boss.

794
00:49:40,081 --> 00:49:44,335
Now that I'm out after all this time,
I have a lot of questions.

795
00:49:44,752 --> 00:49:46,212
What kind of questions, Boss?

796
00:49:46,296 --> 00:49:49,257
How the world has changed
in the last ten years.

797
00:49:49,340 --> 00:49:53,511
Especially everything that happened
with Beom-ryong and Gong-bok.

798
00:49:54,178 --> 00:49:56,514
Tell me everything.

799
00:49:56,848 --> 00:49:58,725
You mean Beom-ryong, sir?

800
00:49:59,100 --> 00:50:01,644
That's right. Beom-ryong.

801
00:50:02,812 --> 00:50:04,105
Didn't you hear me?

802
00:50:05,106 --> 00:50:08,943
I need to know every detail

803
00:50:09,569 --> 00:50:11,946
on what kind of trouble
that runaway kid got into

804
00:50:12,739 --> 00:50:16,534
and who he was running around with.

805
00:50:18,077 --> 00:50:19,245
Sure.

806
00:50:33,468 --> 00:50:36,512
So, have you looked into the ferry case?

807
00:50:36,596 --> 00:50:39,015
Just as you suspected.

808
00:50:39,098 --> 00:50:42,143
An NIS agent and a spy
reportedly went missing on that ferry.

809
00:50:42,226 --> 00:50:43,936
They were reportedly
looking for a package.

810
00:50:44,020 --> 00:50:46,397
It contained information about a traitor
colluding with North Korea.

811
00:50:46,689 --> 00:50:48,650
The package vanished with them.

812
00:50:48,733 --> 00:50:50,860
A traitor colluding with North Korea?

813
00:50:52,320 --> 00:50:53,571
A package?

814
00:50:58,743 --> 00:51:00,828
So how was it all wrapped up?

815
00:51:01,746 --> 00:51:03,915
Deputy Director Han took personal command

816
00:51:03,998 --> 00:51:06,668
and he reportedly kept it
from leaking to the press or the police.

817
00:51:07,210 --> 00:51:11,005
What happened to those
involved in the case afterward

818
00:51:11,089 --> 00:51:12,757
was kept top secret, so nothing is known.

819
00:51:15,551 --> 00:51:18,012
My goodness. Jeez.

820
00:51:19,055 --> 00:51:21,182
The mole is Han Gyeong-wook. Right?

821
00:51:21,432 --> 00:51:24,852
And that package
must contain his weakness.

822
00:51:26,104 --> 00:51:28,439
- Deputy Director Han's weakness?
- Come on, can't you see?

823
00:51:28,523 --> 00:51:31,192
This is exactly
Deputy Director Han's MO, isn't it?

824
00:51:31,275 --> 00:51:33,528
When he fails to retrieve the package
containing his weakness

825
00:51:33,653 --> 00:51:36,864
he takes charge
and buries everyone involved.

826
00:51:36,948 --> 00:51:39,575
What do you think?
Doesn't this picture look familiar?

827
00:51:44,622 --> 00:51:45,623
No, but...

828
00:51:46,582 --> 00:51:50,753
But there's another very
interesting situation to consider here.

829
00:51:50,878 --> 00:51:52,463
Ten years ago

830
00:51:52,547 --> 00:51:55,925
the three people who disappeared
while looking for this package

831
00:51:56,008 --> 00:51:58,469
suddenly reappeared, hand in hand.

832
00:51:59,429 --> 00:52:01,723
What do you think that means?

833
00:52:03,808 --> 00:52:07,395
It means that the package with
Han Gyeong-wook's weakness has surfaced.

834
00:52:11,149 --> 00:52:12,400
Where are the hitmen now?

835
00:52:12,483 --> 00:52:13,985
They're keeping an eye on the three.

836
00:52:15,570 --> 00:52:18,948
There will be a time
when they take out the package.

837
00:52:19,031 --> 00:52:22,285
Tell them to tail them
without missing a single breath

838
00:52:22,368 --> 00:52:25,246
and do whatever it takes
to snatch that package at the right time.

839
00:52:25,329 --> 00:52:27,123
Yes, sir.

840
00:52:30,626 --> 00:52:33,004
The places Bong Je-sun went
are here and here.

841
00:52:33,087 --> 00:52:34,380
Here, here, here, and here.

842
00:52:34,464 --> 00:52:36,841
There aren't many, so it shouldn't
take long to check them all.

843
00:52:44,265 --> 00:52:46,142
- The receiver?
- Oh, one second.

844
00:52:48,811 --> 00:52:50,146
I can't read upside-down.

845
00:52:51,481 --> 00:52:53,316
What does he mean, "not many?"

846
00:52:59,489 --> 00:53:00,990
You've been all over the place.

847
00:53:12,502 --> 00:53:14,462
All right. Here it is.

848
00:53:15,338 --> 00:53:16,380
Well...

849
00:53:18,341 --> 00:53:19,717
Aren't you hungry?

850
00:53:20,301 --> 00:53:21,803
- I'm starving.
- I know, right?

851
00:53:22,470 --> 00:53:25,389
You missed lunch
because you were helping me.

852
00:53:33,064 --> 00:53:36,234
Seriously, who carries around ingredients
for chicken soup in their bag?

853
00:53:36,317 --> 00:53:37,985
I told you.

854
00:53:38,069 --> 00:53:39,946
I wanted to be helpful in any way I could.

855
00:53:40,029 --> 00:53:43,825
Cooking is the only thing I'm good at
so I packed some just in case.

856
00:53:43,908 --> 00:53:45,952
I'm glad they're coming in handy.

857
00:53:46,035 --> 00:53:48,079
Gosh, that looks delicious.

858
00:53:56,420 --> 00:53:58,714
So, how is it? Do you like it?

859
00:53:58,798 --> 00:54:00,216
But there's no black pepper.

860
00:54:00,299 --> 00:54:03,219
- Oh, I...
- No, but it's good enough.

861
00:54:03,302 --> 00:54:04,470
I think it's delicious.

862
00:54:06,013 --> 00:54:07,014
That's a relief.

863
00:54:08,057 --> 00:54:11,060
You stood up for me earlier.
I was really grateful.

864
00:54:11,143 --> 00:54:12,937
Hey, it was nothing.

865
00:54:13,020 --> 00:54:15,773
I mean, Jeong Ho-myeong
isn't usually that rash.

866
00:54:15,857 --> 00:54:18,901
He must be busy and feeling rushed lately
so he made a mistake.

867
00:54:18,985 --> 00:54:20,570
- Was it Bong Je-sun?
- Yes.

868
00:54:20,653 --> 00:54:22,780
- You should try and understand.
- Sure.

869
00:54:22,864 --> 00:54:25,867
Still, it was a very dangerous mistake,
don't you think?

870
00:54:25,950 --> 00:54:28,870
- Oh, it really was dangerous.
- Exactly.

871
00:54:39,881 --> 00:54:43,134
I almost spilled everything myself.

872
00:54:43,843 --> 00:54:44,969
- What?
- What?

873
00:54:50,391 --> 00:54:51,434
Wait.

874
00:55:06,407 --> 00:55:07,617
You saved me.

875
00:55:09,368 --> 00:55:10,620
Hold on.

876
00:55:12,371 --> 00:55:14,540
If it weren't for you guys,
things could have gotten messy.

877
00:55:36,562 --> 00:55:38,314
This ten-year-long ill-fated relationship

878
00:55:39,315 --> 00:55:40,733
and that darn package...

879
00:55:40,816 --> 00:55:43,319
Once you get a good night's sleep

880
00:55:46,238 --> 00:55:48,532
will all be gone.

881
00:56:09,553 --> 00:56:10,638
What should we do?

882
00:56:11,639 --> 00:56:12,974
Just tail him for now.

883
00:56:15,101 --> 00:56:18,688
You need black pepper for chicken soup.

884
00:56:23,985 --> 00:56:25,236
Hey!

885
00:56:25,861 --> 00:56:26,904
Hey!

886
00:56:27,446 --> 00:56:29,198
Hey, Gong-bok.

887
00:56:29,281 --> 00:56:32,576
Hey, Gong-bok, open your eyes! Wake up!

888
00:56:33,119 --> 00:56:35,162
- Darn it.
- Gosh, my head.

889
00:56:37,748 --> 00:56:39,959
- Hang on.
- Gosh, my head.

890
00:56:40,042 --> 00:56:41,877
What the? Where's Bulgae?

891
00:56:42,003 --> 00:56:44,213
Hey, the receiver!

892
00:56:44,296 --> 00:56:45,548
The receiver?

893
00:56:45,631 --> 00:56:46,882
Gosh, hold on.

894
00:56:48,009 --> 00:56:49,635
The receiver is gone.

895
00:56:51,345 --> 00:56:53,180
- What about the car key?
- The car key?

896
00:56:55,725 --> 00:56:56,976
The car key is gone too.

897
00:56:57,935 --> 00:56:59,478
Bulgae, that jerk!

898
00:56:59,687 --> 00:57:01,105
Darn it! Seriously.

899
00:57:49,070 --> 00:57:50,696
What's wrong?

900
00:57:51,864 --> 00:57:53,115
Hey, Bulgae!

901
00:57:55,284 --> 00:57:56,452
Looking for this?

902
00:57:59,038 --> 00:58:02,833
Gosh, Mr. Jeong, Mr. Gang, Mr. Ma.

903
00:58:02,917 --> 00:58:05,169
How... how did you get here?

904
00:58:05,252 --> 00:58:07,421
As for me...

905
00:58:07,505 --> 00:58:09,673
I thought I was starting
to remember something

906
00:58:09,757 --> 00:58:10,925
so I came here for a bit.

907
00:58:11,008 --> 00:58:14,136
Look at that disgusting face.

908
00:58:14,595 --> 00:58:17,640
Well played. You're a really good actor.

909
00:58:19,308 --> 00:58:20,434
Stop the act, you bastard.

910
00:58:20,518 --> 00:58:22,561
Hey, cut it out. We're on to you.

911
00:58:25,648 --> 00:58:27,733
I knew I should've used more of the drug.

912
00:58:30,444 --> 00:58:31,821
Darn it.

913
00:58:33,739 --> 00:58:35,282
How did you know to come here?

914
00:58:35,366 --> 00:58:37,201
I knew you'd pull something like this

915
00:58:38,160 --> 00:58:39,912
so I set up a little trick of my own.

916
00:58:54,885 --> 00:58:56,804
Hey, give that back now.
It belongs to my son.

917
00:58:59,932 --> 00:59:03,435
You darn scumbags. You dare mess with me?

918
00:59:04,812 --> 00:59:07,898
Look at that.
He's finally baring his fangs.

919
00:59:08,023 --> 00:59:10,109
Look at this two-faced jerk.

920
00:59:10,192 --> 00:59:12,903
Gosh, your true nature is coming out now.

921
00:59:13,404 --> 00:59:15,489
This is good. Very good.

922
00:59:15,573 --> 00:59:16,991
Hey, your acting was really...

923
00:59:18,117 --> 00:59:19,702
I almost fell for it.

924
00:59:20,286 --> 00:59:22,496
Did you really?

925
00:59:22,580 --> 00:59:24,290
Now, cut the crap.

926
00:59:24,748 --> 00:59:26,917
At first, I wasn't sure.

927
00:59:27,293 --> 00:59:30,754
But something about what happened
at the hospital kept bothering me.

928
00:59:30,838 --> 00:59:33,924
A guy who ditches a tracker and runs away

929
00:59:34,008 --> 00:59:35,968
suddenly comes back
and offers to help us with our job?

930
00:59:36,051 --> 00:59:37,469
Why would you do that?

931
00:59:37,553 --> 00:59:39,513
It was because
you didn't have the package.

932
00:59:39,597 --> 00:59:42,057
You only knew
the general area of the package

933
00:59:42,141 --> 00:59:43,809
not its exact location.

934
00:59:44,268 --> 00:59:47,062
So I decided to run a little test.

935
00:59:49,190 --> 00:59:51,358
A test? What kind of test?

936
00:59:51,442 --> 00:59:55,988
Hey, why do you think I'd invite
a dangerous guy like you to our hideout?

937
01:00:12,546 --> 01:00:14,798
I said go on ahead.
The three of us need to talk.

938
01:00:16,091 --> 01:00:18,093
I'll be in there, then.

939
01:00:20,721 --> 01:00:22,640
Man, those must be heavy.

940
01:00:41,700 --> 01:00:43,661
Where did they hide it?

941
01:00:45,996 --> 01:00:47,873
They've hidden it really well.

942
01:00:49,250 --> 01:00:50,501
Jeez.

943
01:00:53,295 --> 01:00:55,589
You must have needed this receiver.

944
01:00:56,590 --> 01:01:00,552
Coming here... Jeez, now I get it.

945
01:01:01,512 --> 01:01:02,596
So then...

946
01:01:02,972 --> 01:01:05,432
provoking me like a madman was also...

947
01:01:05,557 --> 01:01:08,227
I figured you'd move
as soon as you felt cornered.

948
01:01:08,310 --> 01:01:09,645
And...

949
01:01:09,728 --> 01:01:13,691
I also had a hunch
you'd ditch these idiots.

950
01:01:16,151 --> 01:01:17,611
Hey, what's that supposed to mean?

951
01:01:17,695 --> 01:01:19,947
If you knew that,
you should've told us beforehand.

952
01:01:20,030 --> 01:01:21,156
Hey.

953
01:01:21,907 --> 01:01:23,575
If you don't want to die,
hand over that receiver.

954
01:01:23,659 --> 01:01:25,202
This guy... He still doesn't get it.

955
01:01:25,286 --> 01:01:26,996
Hey, you think we have to give it to you
just because you ask?

956
01:01:27,079 --> 01:01:29,623
Why are we listening to him?
Let's just crush him already.

957
01:01:29,915 --> 01:01:33,294
Hey, Bulgae.
Why are you after the package?

958
01:01:34,753 --> 01:01:36,463
That USB drive
with Han Gyeong-wook's weakness

959
01:01:36,547 --> 01:01:37,965
is useless to you.

960
01:01:38,882 --> 01:01:40,592
What you're after

961
01:01:40,676 --> 01:01:43,679
is the North Korean slush fund
that Black Pearl brought.

962
01:01:44,221 --> 01:01:45,597
Slush fund?

963
01:01:48,142 --> 01:01:49,935
Slush fund? What are you talking about?

964
01:01:50,019 --> 01:01:51,645
- I'll give it all to you.
- Mr. Jeong. But...

965
01:01:51,729 --> 01:01:53,272
Hey, how much is it?

966
01:01:53,355 --> 01:01:55,316
You can't just make a decision
on something important by yourself!

967
01:01:55,441 --> 01:01:57,568
It's not like we need it anyway.

968
01:01:58,610 --> 01:02:01,739
In return, you'll cooperate with us.

969
01:02:02,781 --> 01:02:06,368
If you help us drive Han Gyeong-wook
out of Yeongseon Island

970
01:02:06,577 --> 01:02:10,456
I'll give you the entire slush fund
after it's all over.

971
01:02:15,127 --> 01:02:17,629
- And you expect me to believe that?
- Make your choice!

972
01:02:19,340 --> 01:02:21,300
If you run away now

973
01:02:21,383 --> 01:02:23,344
your nephew Heo Nam-il on Yeongseon Island

974
01:02:23,427 --> 01:02:25,179
the K-pop dance club members
who helped you

975
01:02:25,262 --> 01:02:28,849
and even Prosecutor Gang
could all get hurt by Han Gyeong-wook.

976
01:02:29,516 --> 01:02:31,101
And you don't want that to happen, do you?

977
01:02:33,395 --> 01:02:37,107
How would you know
if Han Gyeong-wook will hurt Nam-il?

978
01:02:37,191 --> 01:02:40,444
Gosh, this idiot is so paranoid.

979
01:02:40,527 --> 01:02:42,571
See for yourself

980
01:02:42,654 --> 01:02:45,074
just how serious this situation is.

981
01:02:47,034 --> 01:02:48,952
Come out, you rats!

982
01:02:50,204 --> 01:02:51,455
What the hell are you saying?

983
01:02:57,836 --> 01:03:00,297
Mr. Jeong, who are they?

984
01:03:00,381 --> 01:03:01,507
I don't know.

985
01:03:01,590 --> 01:03:03,801
They've been following us
from the camper van.

986
01:03:03,884 --> 01:03:05,803
Hey, we've been tailed this whole time?

987
01:03:05,886 --> 01:03:07,179
You think they were just tailing us?

988
01:03:08,889 --> 01:03:11,683
You're the ones
who messed with the camper, aren't you?

989
01:03:16,939 --> 01:03:19,316
You left traces all over the place.

990
01:03:29,284 --> 01:03:32,704
Hey, did Han Gyeong-wook send those guys?

991
01:03:33,622 --> 01:03:35,582
Sneaking around
and testing the waters like a rat

992
01:03:35,666 --> 01:03:37,126
isn't Han Gyeong-wook's style.

993
01:03:40,754 --> 01:03:41,755
Hey!

994
01:03:41,839 --> 01:03:43,424
You should at least introduce yourselves.

995
01:03:44,299 --> 01:03:45,634
Who sent you?

996
01:03:45,717 --> 01:03:47,010
None of your business.

997
01:03:47,094 --> 01:03:51,557
Hand over the receiver or whatever it is
that can find the package.

998
01:03:52,141 --> 01:03:53,517
Then I'll spare your lives.

999
01:03:53,600 --> 01:03:56,603
What kind of crap are these rats spouting?

1000
01:03:56,728 --> 01:03:59,481
Let's just take them all out,
Bulgae and these scumbags.

1001
01:03:59,565 --> 01:04:00,566
Hey, Bulgae.

1002
01:04:01,066 --> 01:04:02,317
Now make your choice.

1003
01:04:02,985 --> 01:04:05,612
You can either fight against us

1004
01:04:06,488 --> 01:04:09,408
or join us and fight against them.

1005
01:04:21,545 --> 01:04:24,256
SPECIAL THANKS
TO KIM SANG-KYUNG AND KWON YUL

1006
01:04:38,854 --> 01:04:39,855
Found it.

1007
01:04:39,938 --> 01:04:41,607
We've detected a signal
trying to decrypt the package.

1008
01:04:41,690 --> 01:04:43,358
- So it wasn't a bluff?
- Hey!

1009
01:04:43,442 --> 01:04:44,693
- Are you sure you can crack this?
- Huh?

1010
01:04:44,776 --> 01:04:47,154
- This thing isn't easy to open.
- It's almost done.

1011
01:04:47,237 --> 01:04:48,614
- It's 2%.
- Hey, don't touch it.

1012
01:04:48,697 --> 01:04:50,199
If you're trying
to pull a fast one on me...

1013
01:04:50,282 --> 01:04:51,325
We shouldn't be
fighting amongst ourselves!

1014
01:04:51,408 --> 01:04:52,534
The boss got out of prison.

1015
01:04:52,618 --> 01:04:54,244
Bring me that package.

1016
01:04:54,328 --> 01:04:55,746
What if they decide
to side with the thugs?

1017
01:04:55,829 --> 01:04:57,998
You want me to stab my boss
in the back after all this time?

1018
01:04:58,081 --> 01:05:00,334
- Go back to the convenience store.
- I'll step aside.

1019
01:05:00,417 --> 01:05:01,418
Boss!

1020
01:05:01,502 --> 01:05:03,253
- A family?
- Do whatever it takes...

1021
01:05:03,337 --> 01:05:04,338
Get rid of them all.

1022
01:05:04,421 --> 01:05:05,797
What if your family gets hurt first?

1023
01:05:05,881 --> 01:05:07,257
- Ji-woo?
- Dad.

1024
01:05:07,341 --> 01:05:09,218
You don't mind
never seeing your nephew again?

1025
01:05:09,301 --> 01:05:11,678
You think I'd let some useless emotion
hold me back now?

1026
01:05:11,762 --> 01:05:13,180
All I have to do is hand over the package?

1027
01:05:13,263 --> 01:05:15,599
Isn't it a shame?
After all your hard work.

1028
01:05:15,682 --> 01:05:16,725
I'm prepared.

1029
01:05:16,808 --> 01:05:18,477
Let those punks come at us.

1030
01:05:18,560 --> 01:05:19,853
There's nothing we can't do.

1031
01:05:19,937 --> 01:05:21,355
We have to finish this.

